Jacques Burger received a one-week ban for striking Racing Metro scrum-half Maxime Machenaud on Sunday . 
  The Namibia flanker will be available to face Clermont Auvergne in the semi-final on April 18 . 
  Burger was cited for the offence but will not miss Saracens' Aviva Premiership clash with Leicester on Saturday . 
  Sarries beat Racing Metro 24-16 in the Champions Cup on Sunday  . 
 